# Gmail DOM Parsing

## Approach
- Gmail's DOM is unstable — always use multiple fallback selectors.
- Guard every `querySelector` result with null checks.
- Content scripts run in Chrome's isolated world (no access to Gmail's JS).

## Key Selectors
- Message bodies: `.a3s`
- Message containers: `[data-message-id]`
- Sender name: `.gD`
- Thread wrapper: `[role="main"] [role="list"]`
- Collapsed messages: `.kv`, `.gs`, `.hX`
- Hidden messages button: `.adS`, `span.adx`, `[data-collapsed]`
- Current user: `[aria-label*="Google Account"]`, `[email]`

## Thread Expansion
- Two-phase: first click the "N hidden messages" button (`.adS`), then expand individual collapsed messages.
- `expandHiddenMessagesButton()` handles the numbered circle Gmail shows in long threads.
- `expandAllMessages()` uses a `WeakSet` to track clicked elements.
- A stability counter breaks the loop when message count stops changing.
- Always test with short threads, long threads (with hidden messages), and single-message threads.
- Never click "show trimmed content" — trimmed content confuses the model.
